\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-001: DISCOVER N+1 Query Pattern (Performance)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f1  FIXED \'97 commit 
\f3\fs26 d619b36
\f1\fs24  
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  High \'97 caused apparent hangs on entities with >10 outbound edges 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026\

\f0\b Symptom:
\f1\b0  Outbound DISCOVER on high-edge-count entities appeared to hang indefinitely. An entity with 10+ outbound edges would never return.\

\f0\b Root cause:
\f1\b0  
\f3\fs26 Cqr.Repo.Semantic.related_entities/3
\f1\fs24  issued one extra Cypher query per returned row to check scope visibility (an N+1 pattern in 
\f3\fs26 maybe_filter_entities_by_scope
\f1\fs24 ). A hub entity with N outbound edges fired N+1 serialized NIF round trips through the Grafeo GenServer. Past ~10k edges, the accumulated cost pushed DISCOVER past the 30s GenServer call timeout.\

\f0\b Fix:
\f1\b0  Rewrote 
\f3\fs26 related_entities/related_entities_inbound
\f1\fs24  as a single scope-filtered Cypher query. Inlined the IN_SCOPE join into the traversal MATCH with 
\f3\fs26 WHERE s.path IN [...]
\f1\fs24  filter. Added 
\f3\fs26 RETURN DISTINCT
\f1\fs24  to collapse Cartesian-product rows from multi-scope entities. Added LIMIT for bounded result sets.\

\f0\b Performance:
\f1\b0  10,000-edge hub: 472ms (N+1) 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  38ms (single query). 12x improvement.\

\f0\b Tests added:
\f1\b0  
\f3\fs26 test/integration/discover_high_degree_test.exs
\f1\fs24  \'97 hubs with 100, 1000, and 10000 DERIVED_FROM edges.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

