\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f1  FIXED \'97 commit 
\f3\fs26 004b78f
\f1\fs24  
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Critical \'97 all MCP responses with duplicate edge targets appeared to hang 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026 (root cause found after ~8 hours of debugging)\

\f0\b Symptom:
\f1\b0  Outbound DISCOVER hangs when an entity has two different relationship types pointing to the SAME target entity (e.g., DERIVED_FROM 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  nps AND DEPENDS_ON 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  nps). The query worked in 
\f3\fs26 mix run -e
\f1\fs24  and 
\f3\fs26 mix test
\f1\fs24  but hung through MCP.\

\f0\b Root cause:
\f1\b0  When DISCOVER returned duplicate edge targets (same entity reached by DERIVED_FROM + typed relationship), 
\f3\fs26 Engine.merge_results
\f1\fs24  built a 
\f3\fs26 conflicts
\f1\fs24  list containing nested maps with 
\f3\fs26 entity: \{"product", "nps"\}
\f1\fs24  tuples. 
\f3\fs26 format_value/1
\f1\fs24  in 
\f3\fs26 CqrMcp.Tools
\f1\fs24  lacked a clause for plain maps, so nested maps kept raw tuples. 
\f3\fs26 Jason.encode!
\f1\fs24  crashed with 
\f3\fs26 Protocol.UndefinedError
