\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-003: Zombie BEAM Processes Serving Stale Code (Operational)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f1  RESOLVED \'97 operational procedure documented 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  High \'97 caused hours of false debugging 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026\

\f0\b Symptom:
\f1\b0  Code fixes confirmed by 
\f3\fs26 mix test
\f1\fs24  appeared to have no effect when tested through MCP. Features that passed all tests would hang or behave incorrectly through the live MCP server.\

\f0\b Root cause:
\f1\b0  Multiple BEAM processes accumulated from parallel Claude Code sessions, each running 
\f3\fs26 mix run --no-halt
\f1\fs24 . Up to 14 simultaneous BEAM processes observed. Claude Desktop connected to whichever process happened to be listening, usually an old one compiled hours earlier without the latest fixes.\

\f0\b Fix:
\f1\b0  Operational procedure: always run 
\f3\fs26 pkill -9 -f "beam.smp"
\f1\fs24  before testing. Verify with 
\f3\fs26 ps aux | grep beam | grep -v grep
\f1\fs24 . Only then start a fresh 
\f3\fs26 mix run --no-halt
\f1\fs24 .\

\f0\b Impact:
\f1\b0  This single operational issue consumed approximately 6 hours of debugging time across the two-day build session, as bugs appeared to persist after fixes were merged and compiled.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-004: Grafeo NIF Blocks BEAM Scheduler (Architectural Constraint)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9888 \u65039 
\f1  KNOWN CONSTRAINT \'97 documented, not fixable at application layer 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Medium \'97 affects timeout mechanisms 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026\

\f0\b Description:
\f1\b0  The Grafeo NIF is scheduled as 
\f3\fs26 DirtyIo
\f1\fs24 . While this frees normal scheduler threads, the BEAM still cannot preempt, interrupt, or kill a process executing inside the NIF. This means all Elixir-side timeout mechanisms (GenServer.call timeout, Task.yield, Task.shutdown(:brutal_kill), receive/after) cannot catch a NIF that hangs \'97 they fire on the caller side but the NIF-executing process never checks its mailbox until the native code returns.\

\f0\b Mitigation:
\f1\b0  The 3s handler timeout in 
\f3\fs26 handler.ex
\f1\fs24  uses 
\f3\fs26 spawn + receive/after 3_000
\f1\fs24 . If the NIF returns within 3 seconds, the timeout works correctly. If the NIF itself hangs (which has not been observed with the Jason fix), the spawned process is orphaned. The MCP handler returns a clean timeout error regardless.\

\f0\b Impact on development:
\f1\b0  This constraint invalidated four successive timeout implementation attempts (BUG-002 failed fixes #1-4) before the actual root cause (Jason serialization) was identified.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-005: Free-Text DISCOVER Doesn't Find Asserted Entities\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u55357 \u56628 
\f1  OPEN \'97 prompt written, not yet fixed 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Medium \'97 asserted entities invisible to BM25/vector DISCOVER 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 12, 2026\

\f0\b Symptom:
\f1\b0  Entities created via 
\f3\fs26 cqr_assert
\f1\fs24  are fully accessible via RESOLVE and graph DISCOVER (outbound/inbound), but do NOT appear in free-text DISCOVER results. BM25 and HNSW vector search only return seeded entities, never asserted ones.\

\f0\b Reproduction:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 ASSERT entity:project:test TYPE policy DESCRIPTION "worktree management policy" ...\
DISCOVER "worktree"  
\f5 \uc0\u8594 
\f3  returns seeded entities only, not the asserted entity\
RESOLVE entity:project:test 
\f5 \uc0\u8594 
\f3  works correctly\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Likely root cause:
\f1\b0  The free-text DISCOVER path runs a scope-filtered Cypher query to get the candidate set, then computes BM25 and vector similarity in Elixir. Asserted entities at the root 
\f3\fs26 company
\f1\fs24  scope may not match the scope filter correctly in the 
\f3\fs26 search_discover
\f1\fs24  Cypher query path, even though the root scope IS in the visible scopes list.\

\f0\b Prompt written:
\f1\b0  
\f3\fs26 /mnt/user-data/outputs/fix-freetext-discover-asserted-prompt.md
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
