\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-009: Async MCP Handler Race Condition\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f1  FIXED \'97 reverted approach 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Medium \'97 requests processed out of order 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026\

\f0\b Description:
\f1\b0  An attempt to fix the MCP hang (BUG-002) by making 
\f3\fs26 handle_info
\f1\fs24  async via 
\f3\fs26 spawn
\f1\fs24  caused DISCOVER requests to fire before ASSERT operations completed. The MCP server's request ordering guarantee was broken.\

\f0\b Root cause:
\f1\b0  When 
\f3\fs26 handle_info
\f1\fs24  spawns an unlinked process for each request, sequential requests (ASSERT then immediately DISCOVER) execute concurrently. The DISCOVER can run before the ASSERT's Grafeo writes commit.\

\f0\b Fix:
\f1\b0  Reverted to synchronous 
\f3\fs26 handle_info
\f1\fs24 . The actual hang was caused by BUG-002 (Jason crash), not by blocking I/O.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

