\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-011: Grafeo v0.5 Inline Cosine Similarity Gap\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9888 \u65039 
\f1  KNOWN LIMITATION \'97 workaround in place 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Low \'97 affects performance at scale, not correctness 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 8, 2026 (during patent validation)\

\f0\b Description:
\f1\b0  Grafeo v0.5.34 does not support inline cosine similarity computation within Cypher queries. The CQR adapter works around this by retrieving embedding properties and computing cosine similarity in Elixir application code.\

\f0\b Impact:
\f1\b0  At small dataset sizes (thousands of entities per scope), this is fast. At millions of entities, this would require Grafeo to support native vector queries inside Cypher.\

\f0\b Workaround:
\f1\b0  Application-layer cosine similarity in 
\f3\fs26 lib/adapter/grafeo.ex
\f1\fs24 . Documented in the patent as a v0.5 gap.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 BUG-012: ETS Scope Tree Stale After Direct Grafeo Writes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Status:
\f1\b0  
\f2 \uc0\u9888 \u65039 
\f1  KNOWN LIMITATION \'97 by design for V1 
\f0\b Severity:
\f1\b0  Low \'97 only affects non-standard write paths 
\f0\b Discovered:
\f1\b0  April 11, 2026\

\f0\b Description:
\f1\b0  The scope tree is loaded into ETS on startup and invalidated by CERTIFY operations that modify the scope hierarchy. However, if scope nodes are created directly via Grafeo Cypher queries (bypassing the engine), the ETS cache becomes stale until the next restart.\

\f0\b Impact:
\f1\b0  Not a real-world issue \'97 all scope modifications go through the engine in production. Only affects development/debugging where raw Cypher is used to manipulate scope nodes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

